    <text>
        <body>
            <head>189. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName>) to President
                    <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d189fn1">Source: National Security
                    Council, Box SR 095, NSDD 267. Secret. Sent for action. Prepared by <persName
                        corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName>. Copied to <persName
                        corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName> and Senator <persName
                        corresp="recEQQb67MTNPG0x8">Baker</persName>. A stamped notation indicates
                        <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> saw the memorandum
                    on April 9.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="simple_right #right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1987-04-08"
                        >April 8, 1987</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Guidance for the Upcoming <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN"
                        >Shultz</persName>/<persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc"
                        >Shevardnadze</persName> Meeting in Moscow</item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>To document your recent decisions concerning our negotiating positions and provide
                instructions for Secretary <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>’
                impending trip to Moscow.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Background</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">The Secretary</persName> of State departs on
                11 April 1987 for meetings in Moscow with Foreign Minister <persName
                    corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevardnadze</persName>.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>Your review of our arms reductions negotiating position has resulted in adjustments
                to our positions in the areas of <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss>, <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs> and
                    <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recFUg0jqFk2tUZ15">nuclear testing</rs>.
                Attached (<hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab A</hi>)<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d189fn2">Printed as <ref target="#d190">Document 190</ref>.</note> is a
                draft NSDD to document and disseminate your decisions.</p>
            <pb facs="0865" n="838" xml:id="pg_838"/>
            <p>The draft is deliberately brief, simply documenting your decisions without providing
                extensive details. With regard to <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">nonwithdrawal</rs> from the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1"
                    >ABM</gloss>
                <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">Treaty</rs>, it includes the
                safeguards we discussed earlier today and reflects your recognition, following
                extensive discussions both today and previously, that the issue is primarily
                political and diplomatic, rather than technical.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="2">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>That you sign the attached NSDD documenting your approval of the
                        instructions for Secretary <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN"
                            >Shultz</persName>’ Moscow meeting.<note n="3" place="foot"
                            xml:id="d189fn3">
                            <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed his
                            approval.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
